However, this will not work as expected because the SET data type does not support concatenation in this way.

To add a new value to an existing SET column, you need to use the `FIND_IN_SET` function and the `SET` function. Here's how you can do it:

```sql
UPDATE table_name
SET column_name = SET(
    column_name,
    'new_value'
)
WHERE condition;
```

This will add the new value to the existing values in the SET column. Note that if the new value is already present in the column, it will not be added again.

